import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['home_score'], bins=range(0, 12), edgecolor='black', color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['home_score'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Home Scores')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home scores?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['away_score'], bins=range(0, 11), edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['away_score'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['away_score'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Away Scores')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of away scores?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['score_difference'], bins=range(-9, 9), edgecolor='black', color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.xlabel('Score Difference')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of score differences?', wrap=True)
    plt.axvline(data['score_difference'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['score_difference'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['home_score'])
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Home Score')
    plt.title('What is the trend of home scores over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    data['away_score_mean'] = data['away_score'].rolling(window=10).mean()
    
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['away_score_mean'], label='Away Score Mean')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Away Score Mean')
    plt.title('What is the trend of away scores over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
